message.content:
1. A significant gain of CAL was seen in Group B.
2. The gain of CAL in Group B was 2.23 ± 0.75 mm.
3. The P-value for the gain of CAL in Group B was less than 0.001.
4. A significant gain of CAL was also seen in Group A.
5. The gain of CAL in Group A was 1.60 ± 0.86 mm.
6. The P-value for the gain of CAL in Group A was less than 0.001.
7. There was a significant difference between the gains of CAL in Group A and Group B.
8. The P-value for the difference between the gains of CAL in Group A and Group B was less than 0.01.
